      <h6>
        Cristiano Ronaldo is a Portuguese professional footballer widely
        regarded as one of the greatest players of all time. Known for his
        incredible skill, speed, and goal-scoring ability, he has played for top
        clubs such as Manchester United, Real Madrid, Juventus, and Al-Nassr.
        Ronaldo has won numerous prestigious awards, including multiple Ballon
        d'Or titles, and has set records for most goals in both the UEFA
        Champions League and international football for Portugal. His relentless
        work ethic and leadership on and off the pitch have made him a global
        sports icon.
      </h6>
      <br />
      <h3>Career Highlights</h3>

      <h6>
        Cristiano Ronaldo, one of the greatest footballers in history, has had
        an illustrious career. Starting at Sporting Lisbon, he gained global
        recognition at Manchester United, winning three Premier League titles
        and a Champions League, along with his first Ballon d'Or in 2008. At
        Real Madrid, he won four Champions League titles, became the club’s
        all-time top scorer, and secured four more Ballon d'Ors. After success
        in Italy with Juventus, Ronaldo returned to Manchester United,
        surpassing 800 career goals. Internationally, he led Portugal to Euro
        2016 and the Nations League 2019, becoming the all-time top
        international goal scorer.
      </h6>
      <div class="collapse" id="sajan">
        <h6>
          Cristiano Ronaldo’s career is marked by extraordinary achievements,
          both at the club and international levels. He has won five Ballon d'Or
          awards, cementing his place among football’s elite. With Manchester
          United, he claimed three Premier League titles and a Champions League
          victory in 2008. During his time at Real Madrid, Ronaldo won four
          Champions League titles, becoming the club’s all-time top scorer with
          450 goals. He also found success in Italy, winning two Serie A titles
          with Juventus. Internationally, Ronaldo led Portugal to their first
          major trophy at Euro 2016 and added the UEFA Nations League in 2019,
          while becoming the all-time top scorer in international football. His
          consistent ability to perform in different leagues and competitions
          highlights his unmatched talent and dedication to the sport.
        </h6>
      </div>
